content: This is an awesome game I have it on play pass. The only thing is after you get all the upgrades its kind of the same after so long. I have over 300 gems but nothing to do with them. If the developers add like boosts, saves, and/or other new obstacles that would be awesome. Over all great game
Polished and fun, based on a tried and true concept... but too short for what they're charging. I would have liked to see more planets and maybe some planet-specific mechanics.
Very fun game...last level is impossible with all of the upgrades... So uninstalling
Solidly wasted time at the doc office

Great game but it can have errors. Sometimes, pieces that should fall don't, but usually they disappear if they get to the top. Just now though, I lost a game when there were no pieces even near the top. If the glitches were fixed this would be five stars.
It has alimit only fun for a few days not qorth 3 dollars
It's a cool game keep up the work and hope for good stuff in the next update
Fun twist on a classic concept

Very fun game. Not stressful and can be combined with other activities like an audiobook etc. Only four stars because I don't like the interface. You can't restart a game for no good reason, and quitting and restarting the app gets you exactly where you left off. This is somewhat good but at one point I got some kind of error and since you can't really quit the game like any decent app, I had to reinstall and start the game all over. Also the little figure in the bottom is useless.

Rigged worse with game pass. I had to use game guardian to cheat gems and still could not advance further than the 3rd planet. With 32 balls, and infinite shots it throws screwed in bars with hundreds of hits required. This is imposible. I don't know if since it is free with the pass it is made harder without extra in app purchases revenue. Or if it is rigged against you from the start for ads in the nonplay pass version. I would have never mined the first moon with out game guardian.
Can't sync/save data
Gray style, gray soundtrack, and very nice gameplay
Simply addicting. Watching the balls bounce and wreck everything is even more satisfying than breakout.
Broken game. If it ever freezes once you have to uninstall to play again. Skip this garbage.
I think this would be much more fun with longer maximum flight time and non-rounded tiles
It's okay
Way too short of a game for that kinda money
Boring, just boring, got some swing but neah starting is to slow

Love the sounds of the bubbles! Low stress game that can encourage your competitive spirit. I wish there were more planets to play, the endless is nice, but now I have all these coins and cant spens them :( Other than that, great for subway, or wait rooms. Have fun!!
Fun game but not nearly enough content. Especially something they're charging for. Disappointing

It was a fun game, for about 3 days. I beat all the levels pretty quickly. If i paid 3.99 for it i would be mad but its on the playpass for free so im ok with it. I would love to see some more content
Absolutely terrible progression
Would give 5 stars but need more levels. I love this game. Challenging yet not impossible.
Juegazo
incredibly addictive. played through all levels and still playing just to see the 99 balls bouncing around. please make more levels. please....
Great game, but way too short.
I think this is a really fun time waster. I understand the people complaining about price , because there isnt much replay value, but I got it on the play pass - so its a great find for me!
I wish it had more lvls and more upgrades

I wish there was more content. I still come back to endless mode once in awhile, but I'd really like more levels, maybe with different shapes. The core gameplay is fun and the game is not an endless money sink or ad-ridden nightmare. Thanks for making it!

The game feels good to play and is very polished. To me what holds it back is the lack of depth, funny for a game about digging. It would've been OK if the game sold for ‚Ç¨1 to ‚Ç¨3 but for ‚Ç¨4.50 I expected a little more variety. When I saw that there were different planets to explore I thought they would feature special blocks to make them feel different or have unique bosses but no, planets just get bigger and harder. Not a bad game, it just got repetitive fairly quickly for me.
This game is the new Tetris for me, I just played and played until I finished. Worst part is that there isn't enough of the game to keep playing. An update with more challenges would be amazing!

Fun but short little game... Get to the end pretty quickly. Biggest annoyance is a failsafe that returns balls that hit only the sides several times so they don't get "stuck" -- it kicks in WAY to soon, often the balls are making clear progress towards the balls below (20-30¬∞ angle!) and suddenly they're out! It's not uncommon to only have bricks at top and bottom given the fall mechanic; give it a chance!
A perfect example of a polished and fun game, and from a single-person team above all!
It's a fun game, that's mostly short and greta for bus rides!

It's really polished and fun... for the first hour. Pretty soon you reach the infinite black hole stage and have all the upgrades, and the only reasons you have to keep playing are to get a high score and/or to kill time. No replay value at all. I'd give it 5 stars if it cost $1, maybe even $2. Definitely not worth $4 though.
Animation, sound and music all great, simple addicting gameplay, wish there were more levels and different upgrades.
Don't pay for this. The developers have gone on holiday
satisfying
Brilliant. So simple, only fairly short but great replay value. Lovely, lovely game
this is the worst version of games like this
Great fun but needs infinite upgrades
Awesome game. Great time killer. Super fun and does not overly kill battery which is great.
Great game. Wish it was longer though!
After a few seconds the screen gets extremely narrow and the game becomes unplayable.

A game that I "finished" in a day, and enjoyed the whole time. I personally wasn't super keen on the endless mode (which is why I deleted the game) but it's super charming with good controls, and I liked the sound design as well.
A fun, low stress game with nice visual elements. The lack of a restart option is pretty silly though. I should've be forced to play to the end of a game I know I've lost.
Great, quick game. I got to the black hole and unlocked all upgrades in about a week. I wish there was a larger map (wider, not longer) to play in.
Endless fun, one of the only games that has consistently traveled from phone to phone with me.
Just wish there were more levels/things toget with the gems... bought all the upgrades and am on the blackhole but can barely get past 500
Me and my husband love the game. My only question is what is the little character in the bottom right corner. My husband thinks ghost and I think thumb.
Meh
Fun and addictive game. I hope you guys plan on adding more features and themed planets. üòÉ
So, I absolutely love this little game. I play it randomly, but I really wish there were more levels since I've completed everything but that vicious black hole. Ha.
Needs more content, the endless lvl is to easy to access and then the game is boring.

Fun, but super easy, then super difficult. I'm at the end of the game and I have every upgrade maxed but it barely makes a difference in the stage. Trust me, I don't mind a grind but the blocks are stacked in ways are are impossible to break them. I understand it's supposed to take a really long time to break through that stage, but it shouldn't be impossible or something you can only achieve if you get lucky. As for everything else I wish there were other upgradable elements and more stages.
It's fun, but I played it trough play pass, it's pretty short. Would be nice if the upgrades were endless, especially the starting number of balls.

Over too quickly. Even after the infinite level is reached, there are no longer any upgrades. So you can play indefinitely on the infinite level, but it gets really boring really fast. I thought since I can keep collecting gems or stones or whatever they're called, that I could eventually use them for an upgrade, but none thus far. I added a star for Play Pass availability, however if I had to pay for the game, I probably would have rated only 2‚≠ê because of how quickly it was over.
Got bored really quickly..
Fun, but runs out of things to do very quickly.
Fun game but too short

I like the idea of the upgrades. Unfortunately quickly becomes quite repetitive. I can't come up with a suggestion but would've liked to see more changes/upgrades and different game mechanics as I progress. Has potential.

Not very playable on s9. Must be the same for all 'long' phones as the text is squashed and barely readable Edit Restarted and works fine now, scaled correctly. Fun to play and endless mode is fun too
Well Designed but short overall.
Pretty fun, but it really needs an option to quit a level
Fun, could be longer. Wish there were different types of upgrades like bombs.

Game works well but seems very limited. There aren't enough upgrades to advance quickly. You have to play the same levels over and over and once you level up, that's it. No more advancement. I'm sure others have beaten the black hole level, but I've given up. Should have saved my $4 for something else.
Great game! Respects your time. I just wish there was something to do with all the gems I earned

Love this game, but loses a star for how quickly you can max out everything and hit a ceiling. Really wish there was more! Dropping it two stars. The infinite level is completely useless. I thought I'd at least have high score to try and beat, but the total randomness makes it awful. Having no upgrade ceiling means I would at least get some improvement and benefit to the grind.
This game does what it does very well, but it's so one-dimensional. It's built well, looks great, and has character, but it gets old fast. This game is just a time-waster. Nothing more, nothing less.

I still keep going back and replaying this even after finishing all the levels few months back. The gameplay experience is just so fun and easy to get into even for a quick minute. The sounds, the graphics and the mechanics are put together really well. If I could wish for anything more for this game, it would be more levels!
Great bit lacks replayability
Fun game. Addictive.

This game is truly delightful in its simplicity. I've been playing on and off for a couple of years now, and I keep coming back to it. It's a wonderful pass time when you want something that you can pick up and put down any time (literally - it saves your state mid-shot!!). It's great for my anxiety, and gives me something to do while relaxing and watching TV or waiting for my code to build.
Boring!
I'm the kind of person that likes to play mindless strategy games to distract their brain from ADHD and anxiety and this game is really doing it for me. Love it

The game itself is very good and a fresh take on the whole breakout genre. Graphics are satisfying and minimalist and gameplay mechanics are very fun and addictive. But that all dies out very quickly once you have broken all the cores in each level. Took me about 2 hours to complete the game and get to the infinite level at the end and then the game loses all appeal and i just uninstalled. Hope I see some updates to keep this game fresh but absolutely would not recommend spending so much money.

I love this game. I never love games or apps or anything other than music. This game is fun. I mean I have to think which is a good thing. For some reason I think the longer you live the less you have to think. But this game is totally worth thinking about. Man it's fun just try it.
Good game, needs more upgrades and levels.
The game doesn't have a lot of depth. (pun intended) While the various upgrades can keep you occupied for a while, ultimately it's not a game of skill ‚Äî you can grind away until you win.

I LOVE THIS GAME BUT THAT'S ALL THERE IS??? ‚òπÔ∏è This game is addictive and made my commute FLY BY every morning! But once I conquered the Sun "level" that was it! You then get put in the Black Hole level which is meaningless. PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE add more levels!!!! And don't hesitate giving this one a go. It's worth it.

It's a cute slick game but gets boring real quick. The mechanic is literally the same from the start to the finish and the only thing that changes throughout each level is that the numbers get bigger. No new mechanics, new challenges, new powers, nothing. Definitely a loss of opportunity.

The game has a very unique concept, its like a progression based breakout. The only issue is once you've done all the upgrades and unlocked the last zone( roughly a took me 4 hours) it just kinda fizzles. Perhaps if the progression was a longer ladder or there was some more unique upgrades I'd give it a 5 star. Overall worth checking out as a time killer.
Jaja Super Fun Game
This was "free with Play Pass" so my 2 stars is based fully on not getting the "3 crystals in one round" on the first level after maxing out my stats and getting 3 crystals in one round.
Fun few first levels, then becomes a grind fest. Hey Devs, lower the point totals on the planet level, it's so boring losing over and over again trying to collect crystals.
Its fun for a while but it gets kinda old fast.
Needs balancing, far too difficult
So much fun and relaxing! Only critique is the "campaign" is over too soon!
It's an okay game, never played one of these before and don't really get the appeal
Beat the game but I still keep coming back to play the endless mode. I just wish there was a little more to do once you break all the cores and buy all the upgrades.
A lot of fun but has some bugs where it doesn't always clear blocks when it should. üò≠
It seemed very enjoyable and cute to me. I wish there was more to it though.

Fun, lightweight, challenging after the initial learning curve. You think you know how to break blocks, but how am I going to get to *that* level of efficiency?!? Shoot deep to destroy lower levels and drop higher levels, "nick" the edges of those blocks to bounce horizontally, and aim to trap the ball on lower levels.

I'm glad I didn't pay any money for this game. It was fun for an afternoon, but once I realized that the last "level" is just an infinite unwinnable thing, the game instantly list its appeal. There's nothing left to strive for. There's no further enhancements to "upgrade" and no feeling of achievement beyond beating your personal best at level of depth. It feels lazy, like very little thought was put into the game design. üëéüèºüëéüèº
Played nonstop until I beat it
Enjoyable but very short and repetitive. Great potential.
A fun game good for killing time.
Highly addictive!!!!! I love it
Love it!
Love going through the levels.
I love this game
Fun but short. The upgrade system works well but there are only a handful of levels. Definitely worth a download.
Fun game, but maxed out upgrades in only 2 sessions. Wish there was more to it.
It won't lode

Game is really good, I appreciate that it saves the game wile playing levels. I have to agree with everyone else though that one you've played through the first level it's all just more of the same. Once you get to the end level there isn't much motivation to keep playing. I think introducing fixed levels and leaderboards might help as well as new block types, maybe ones that can't be broken, spit balls, etc ...
Amazing addictive gameplay!

I've had this since launch, and while at the time I would say that it was well worth it, now somehow the game just flat out runs worse and has crashed my phone a few times. Dunno what exactally the updates have been, but they have made my play experience substantially worse. Worst part is that the frame rate of this 2D game is now unstable with visable dips.
Very relaxing game. I have had it for a long time and still can't beat the last level, but it does exactly what I want it to do.. helps me relax.
Super addictive, awesome design, cute sounds and a fun concept. Only wish there were more levels, maybe different shaped game area instead of just vertical rectangles.
Nothing special. The upgrades don't really add much to the fun, they're kinda boring.

Decent ball drop game. I feel like the angles on the sides of the blocks end up causing 90 degree angles too often, usually shooting your balls back up to the top. Got 4 tries into the black hole and Uninstalled. Probably 8 hours of gameplay.
Fun

I get it there isnt much game here and what is there is very easy. But the addition of endless mode makes it so there is a reason to come back. I finally got a 1000+ meters but it takes so long to get there I am not sure I will be tryin again.

Fun but gets repetitive fast. I think it's good enough as a finished product for a kid to enjoy but some things were mildly frustrating like not being able to speed up the balls and having to wait for tens of balls to do their thing and come back!!! Not that big a deal, really the worst thing is just that there's not much more to do. Each levels the same challenge, just bigger in scale, and even the upgrades are also just the same "powers" you already have, they just get bigger in scale.
It's a interesting shoot the ball and destroy the blocks type game gets kinda repetitive
Boo!
Fun but short you can beat it in a few hours.
Cute addicting game
Honestly holedown is an amazing game. I loved the progression, but it was just over so quickly. I would love to keep playing but there is nothing left to play!
Perfect.

Good idea, but it feels like grinding from the start. You constantly need to upgrade your stats to just complete a single mission/planet, progression limiting seems feels forced. Also feels like it has been built to sell Microtransactions due to the grind.
Good overpriced game. Finished it in 2 hours, now it just takes up space.
Definitely waaaaay too short for a price at all. You'll get to the last level in no time with all of the upgrades, and then you face the brick wall of black hole.
It's a good game, just way too short. Adding more levels would be really easy, not sure why there are so few.
What are you supposed to do with it. Dumb
Very fun for free on Pass
Just wish there was more before or after the black hole. Nice challenging game
Too fast to complete, not enough point in the end game.

Game has drm that prevents offline play. Did not have this before. This game needs no online connection to function. Have uninstalled game in protest. After dev reached out, I will try latest update and see if issue is fixed, and re-evaluate Seems ok so far, have update to a hogher score. Needs more testing
replyContent: I'm sorry I didn't catch this earlier, a connection should absolutely not be required other than on the first startup. Anything other than that is a bug and I would like to apologise for any issues you've had!

content: Best in class! I've played several of these but this is my all-time favorite. Note to developers: speed up gem collection/count at end of game.
the worm is so cool
Simple and fun but there is strategy.
10/10 gameplay and execution. 0/10 infantile communist propaganda.
Lovely game but doesn't last long
Good game but too short and once you beat everything there's not much you can do
Very fun game! But after 3 levels, there's no more challenges. It was fun while it lasted!
Fun but needs more upgrades for more replayability. Some skill based combo system that lets your earn more shots quicker would be cool too.

I've played games like this before, but I really love this one. I burned through all the levels in a day or two, and went back to them til I was less than 10% in each level's leaderboard. Now every day I play the endless (last) level to see how far I can get. It's relaxing & addicting. I wish there were more levels before the last. I wish there was a "vs" mode where two players competed, over days if necessary, and whoever got deeper won something, a trophy? I wish we could submit sayings too!
Fun and addicting. Which is a problem because you can fly through it in a few hours. Too bad. Needs at least 4 times the levels.
Games super fun to just chill on! Wish there were more levels
NO ADS BEST GAME ON GOOGLE PLAY!!! THIS APP HAS GREAT SOUND EFFECTS AND SMOOTH 80FPS FRAME RATES EVEN ON SLOW DEVICES!!
An option to change the blackhole color is needed
Meh, gets boring quickly. Thankfully got this with Google play pass. Otherwise I'd be very upset about 4$ wasted on something meh.

Good game, and hooked on black hole mode. But when you don't have mobile signal it constantly kicks you off and says it can't verify the license. Extremely frustrating. Left feedback for the developer with the issue but had no response.

Requires internet to play. Toddler ran off with my phone and managed to freeze the balls. The game still worked but the balls wouldn't shoot. There isnt a restart level button either. I tried restarting my phone, clearing the cache of the app, force stopping; nothing worked. Forced me to restart my game completely. Aside from that the game is wonderful and polished. I just wish there were more upgrades and maybe some temporary buffs you could get. Maybe a couple more levels too.
A fun, simple game that doesn't outstay its welcome. Graphics are minimalist but charming. No ads or IAP. Well thought out achievements. Definitely worth a try!
Love the game! I haven't gotten very far, some people are complaining that it gets worse after a while, but what I've seen, I love, and won't change my mind even if the game is short or bad later on
Not a bad game. Its a fun twist on a classic. However I got bored fast.
Really fun for a short time. There are only a few levels and then it gets relative in the endgame. Definitely try it if you have play pass, otherwise it's expensive for the amount of play time.

Considering i got this with the play pass rather than paying directly, it's a decent. You can blast through it and it's unique for the brick breaking genre. It does get to some points where it's a grind and either you feel too overpowered or too weak. I do also wish there was an end of the game marker. Like something to pop up and say hey that's all! You dug through the galaxy! The UI is clean with the exception of purchasing; Ie. there should be a way to choose between map and replaying.
Good game. Although it takes a lot of repetitive plays to level up.
Challenging at moments but easily beaten. Not $4 of content by any means. At this stage, it should be a $0.99 game. Shows potential, but it's not reached yet.
Lots of replay value.
Game gets boring before you even get to the third level.
Great game! Wish there were more levels or challenges to increase the amount of replay
Fun
Fun until you unlock everything and reach the blackhole. Then not much to bother with.

This game managed to fix a lot of the problems that people had with games like Ballz, but it ultimately suffers from the same major issue of dragging on endlessly until you sigh and ask yourself, "What is even the point?" The gameplay doesn't change as you progress, and all progression does is make all the blocks have more health, so the game gets even more tedious. You basically just play for an hour until you have an existential crisis and feel dead inside, and that's it.
Got it for free with play pass. Was OK, but I finished it in a few games. Glad I didn't pay for it.
A little "difficult" at first. I almost quit, but it's satisfying after you update and get into it
Wouldn't fit on the screen properly, it's not a phone with a weird aspect ratio either.
Beat game of its type that I've played.
challenging
I thought it was pretty good, well polished game. As others have said, could do with more levels and perhaps something like explosions..
Not compatible for 10+
Fun
This is the most addictive game I've ever played

Pretty good game but gameplay comes to an abrupt end. I get there's a lot of development that goes into even a game like this, but for $3.99 I'd expect more content. Got it for free in play pass and not a bad game in that regard.
Great game. Played it until 1am multiple nights in a row. Great for short intervals, which turn into long intervals with "one more game" addictiveness.
It's a unique take on breakout/brick breaking but it lacks depth, level design could be better, and upgrades are massively unbalanced making gameplay frustrating and occasionally boring.

It's addictive but I just wish there was more to the game; more upgrades, more levels, more objectives, more achievements, more rewards. I have around 700 jewels with nothing to spend them on. At least make some more levels please! Edit: 1,895 jewels and still no substantial update, gotta give just a star... UPDATE THE GAME!
Awesome game. Highly addictive albeit a little short. Adding events or some extra levels would be nice but great game overall and it was free with Google Play Pass so I can't complain.
Brilliant game but not enough levels. I played this quite intensively and beat it in a few days. There's not much replay value so it would benefit greatly with more levels

This is great if you want a casual fast paced break out like game with great visuals, upgrade system but simple. I'm not sure what people's issues are but allot of these negative reviews seem childish and entitled, last I checked they do not charge 5 dollars for higher graphic games like judge or knights of the old republic unless they are on sale. I've seen way worse on here for 5 dollars same goes for on steam. This was not a cheap game to make so the price is most certainly worth it.

Its super fun and addictive gameplay and the worm animation following the balls cracks me up. But like other reviews said its extremely short once it hooks you. I've unlocked everything now I have no incentive to play anymore.
Need to expand endless mode.
Average game at best
For a short game it gets grindy really quickly

As others have said, not much (very similar) content to be had for the price. At best, it's well presented and has a feel of a polished game (albeit temporarily). At worst, it's not even a good as a free equivalent game I've been playing (where I'm still enjoying it on level 600-odd). Uninstalled, as nothing left to do (apart from feel disappointed).
Fun but short! Would love to see more levels.

The game is really fun and addictive. But once you you've completed all the levels and unlock endless mode, the game looses it's fun aspect. There are no more upgrades and just feels incomplete. They need to add more levels and upgrade options
Beautiful simple graphics and rewarding gameplay
You can litterally get a batter version for FREE. And the rounded corners of the blocks ruins it. Also, you need to grind too much. Uninstalled. Glad I got it for free from the play pass.
Good game, wish it was longer.
Great game but now crashes on startup every time and cannot be used.
I beat the WHOLE game in 3 days. Throw on Airplane mode, and in a couple of hours, the game is complete!

By far the most charming ball bouncing game I've played. I love the simple but pleasing art style and upgrading for level progression. I will say for $4 though, I would wish there were more levels to explore with a bit more variety to each planet, but still a fun and addicting way to pass the time

The core mechanic of the game is fun and the presentation is cool however after 6 fairly easy levels the game goes into infinity mode where there's nothing to achieve. The game would've been so much richer with some power-ups and ongoing challenges to keep you engaged. It just feels like the moment you learn the game there's nothing to play for. I don't think it's worth its price in its current state.
Excellent, simple, addictive game without any FTP annoyances.

Simple & addictive, but not $3.99 worth of content. Once you beat Planet, Sun is trivial. Final level is infinite Black hole which is fun for a bit. But by then you've unlocked every upgrade (except 100 ball count), so there's little incentive. Biggest annoyance is that you are penalized for clearing the screen. Also there's no way to exit a game in progress. If you accidentally click "Play again" after you've just beaten a level, tough luck, you'll just have to beat that level again. Just why?

So so so pleasant and relaxing. You can either play to progress and win or just let the balls bounce and see what happens, worst case you just try again. Soundtrack is soothing and hypnotic, and so are the sound effects and visuals.
Very fun and addictive. Wish there were more upgrades and levels. Once you've fully upgraded and breached the core at every level, you're left with just trying to beat your high scores.
sex
Addicting gameplay. Great game for short bursts of free time.

Payed this game a ton in quarantine! Beat all levels in 2-3 days. Been playing black hole a lot but wish there were more levels or upgrades. Almost 5 stars but wish there were more angles the ball would bounce. So many times it comes right back to you. Ok I changed to 5 stars because I've gotten so much play time out of it, but definitely room for improvement.
Core gameplay is addictive. Content is a bit limited but the artstyle and amount of polish is amazing
Game is fun, quick, easy to pick up and play. Great if you have a few minutes a day, or want to come back to it days or weeks later
I love games with fun visuals and sounds! This game and ordia have won me over for those things alone.
It's nice
It starts off strong but you max your upgrades fast and blackhole loses interest after awhile. I think this would be 5 star if they just increased upgrades and added some new levels.

Stylish design and a fun concept initially, but the gameplay wears incredibly thin very, very quickly. Frustrating & repetitive, your progress is often down to pure luck and it feels like you'd do just as well by randomly mashing yr screen.
Really chill experience. Cute and fun.

Great time waster, but it has a few frustrating design decisions. The main one is that clearing a screen actively penalties you: about 6 lines of blocks appear at once and tend to overwhelm you. Doing well requires a weird balance of trying to do well but not too well, which is weird and not super satisfying
The game is fun, but the content runs out super fast.
Very fun game. Beat the whole game in a few days. Worth it
I love it, its fun and very satisfying. Totally worth its price!!
Good game but too short - got to black hole within a couple of hours. Then you lose motivation to play much more really...

Excellent game but new update crashes phone. Would like to see an update/ sequel with different block types (explosive ones, blocks you have to avoid hitting e.g.) which would expand gameplay. Please fix the crashing in the new update though!
Captivating and "moreish". Perfect for mobile
Please add a way to get back to the planet section screen from the game screen
Polished game, quite fun. A bit simplistic and short however
I'm on a note 10, came here from a Northernlion recommendation. It runs very well, very enjoyable little thwaps when the shots connect!

Ok Game, obnoxious DRM. The game is entertaining but shallow, and not more than a few hours of content. But the DRM that prevents me from playing a game I paid for unless I have an internet connection is too much. Your quest to reduce piracy should not come at the price of locking out paying users. Learn how to issue a token. One star.
replyContent:
I'm sorry I didn't catch this earlier, a connection should absolutely not be required other than on the first startup. Anything other than that is a bug and I would like to apologise for any issues you've had!  
If you're still having issues, drop me an email at support@grapefrukt.com and we'll dig deeper.

content: A fun game with no ads or exploitative microtransactions!

Took me way too long to realise that the last level doesn't had an end. Managed to get to 595 metres though. Could do with power ups and special blocks etc. Apart from that it's pretty fun and addictive.

I love the game. It's beautiful, simple, and works very well. I only hope that more content is added soon. More upgrades perhaps. Black hole is good, but the ability to upgrade the balls further would be nice. Maybe even upgrades that effect the properties of the balls?
Simple, good looking, and satisfying.

I bought Holedown in a recent sale and I love it to pieces! Beautiful aesthetic, quick to load, no annoying ads or IAPs. Most of all though, it's just so satisfying to play! I think I'll be chipping away on endless mode forever. A wonderful mobile game overall and I'm keen to try more games from this talented dev.
Saw this game on Northernlion Tries and instantly had to play it. One of the few mobile games that are actually challenging and not in a pay to win way, pure enjoyment and addiction. Great game guys!
I bought this because I saw Egg playing it and thought, "yea, u could do this way better." Turns out it was harder than it looks. Overall a very nice game
Great aesthetics and fun mechanics. One of the best breakout inspired games I've seen. I saw NorthernLion showcase it and I had to get it on mobile.
If there's one thing holedown has taught me, it's that you gotta have balls to win--and winners have a lotta balls.
Fun little ball bouncing game, the farther you get, the more satisfying it gets.
Perfect quick game.
Its a great game. Fun to play and chill. Relaxed. But I can't figure out how to quit from a level and try another.

Amazing game, I love it. Only bringing the rating down to a 4 because it frequently crashes. Not while I'm playing, but very often when I return to my game it loads up where I left off and it's stuck on that screen. Sometimes on the menu, sometimes in a level, but maybe 5 times this has happened today alone. Force closing the app doesn't fix it, I have to restart my whole device.
Visually great, gameplay great, the fact that it took me just three days to get to the end, not so great... Considering the price of this I expected a little more for my money.

I wish somebody had told me this was an updated version of Breakout. Y'know, the game where you have a paddle and a ball and you have to break bricks? I've been playing those games since the mid 80s and it's really cool to see an update to the genre.
Arcadaganza. Great but so repetitive.

A polished take on the popular ball barrage game genre, extremely simplistic in nature but still quite fun. Holedown pairs this basic activity with an upgrade system that ensures you won't get too far too fast. On the one hand, this increases the game's longevity, on the other, it punishes skilled gameplay by preventing you from picking up all the upgrade crystals you see by harshly limiting your maximum yield per round, leading to stale gameplay where you can neither progress nor upgrade.
Forgot I hadn't rated this game, it's probably my favorite android game ever good job dude
Good game, latest version becomes unplayable after just a short time as it slows down to a crawl
Amazing game. Wish there were more levels.
Is good!

Probably the best game out there, in this genre. Controls are tight and visuals are pleasent. Only issue is the content. Please, please, please build some more stuff to do. That being said I still play this game almost daily, since the day the game came out. It's really that good.

Really fun and relaxing. The games got a good soundtrack but it's also fun for listening to podcasts and you just wanna do something with your hands. No ads or dlc bull either. Only thing it needs is some more levels or an expansion and I'd be happy to pay for it if it actually doubled the games size

Simple, fun physics puzzle ... think breakout, but you take turns, and buy upgrades between games ... with no ads or in-app purchases. This is what Android gaming should be!
Great!

Delightful, well polished twist on the brick-breaker genre. Visuals and animations are crisp. Sound design is excellent. A very satisfying experience. Nice that there are goals and upgrades of sorts to keep the player hooked. My only minor gripe, I wish in the endgame / endless mode we could continue upgrading our starting ball count beyond 32. It's been pretty difficult starting against 70+ hp blocks that are already creeping up halfway on the map.
epic game to kill time, please update some new levels, I reached black hole but I don't like to play with no purpose, love this game tho

One of the best.mobile games you can buy. I wish there were more levels!
No replayability. Once the levels are cleared there's no reason to play them again. Maybe if there were a lot more of them it would be fine, but there's just not enough game here for the price.

A brilliant cross between Breakout, Tetris and a pinball machine with a touch of Centipede. Highly addictive and beautifully designed, both visuals and sound. Recommended!

Nice concept and execution. I feel like it doesn't change enough as the game progresses, but the core loop is very fun, and it's great to come back to again and again. I'm glad that the game charges me upfront and then there's no micro-transactions, wouldn't have gotten it otherwise, to be honest. Looking forward to more games from this developer.

There's no way to quit a game without finishing the one you've already started. When you're early in a dig and you make a fatal play, you have to finish the dig before restarting. That's needlessly time consuming, especially as you advance in the game. It's such an easy fix and very frustrating. The developers chose to go another way for the sake of some pet value they have, and that's bad for the player.

best with headphones , love it

fun game w good graphics and sound but gets dull at the end

fun

fun game...

i want my money back i payed for the game and i cant download it waited for over 6 hours with the only description "download pending" have installed other apps in the meantime so i know its mot an issue on my side

very fun, but it ends way way too quick.

Holedown feels great and looks great, but unfortunately loses its flavors by the second or third level. The only thing to unlock with the gems that you collect is the ability to fire more balls. No powers, no interesting obstacles between planets. The name of this game is: make the numbers go higher, but without any meaningful progression. Once you learn how to make the various skill shots, the only thing left is How long can I make the numbers go down in one shot.  I don't regret buying it, I regret the price. Hopefully Holedown 2 is a bit more Peggle 1. Then there would be something to recommend the game. At his point, I would not suggest buying it for anything more that $2.
single mechanic game with cute 2d graphics... way too simple and short though, feels incomplete
so fun and addictive!
very fun. well put together. good game.

A very fun game about recreating the moment when you get the ball in brakout stuck above the top level of bricks, combined with a lot more personality than those games ever had. the endless mode isnt for me, but the progression up to unlocking it was quite enjoyable. definitely worth the askinf price.

fantastic game!

menu, and mute sounds option.

Would really, really like to be able to mute sound effects. Also had game 
glitch and lost all progress, had to uninstall and reinstall. Otherwise 
great, addictive game.
replyContent: I added an option to mute the sound effects in the last update. Sorry it took so long!

content: Really gun

Great execution of the core mechanic, but the lack of progression and short 
game-length make it not worth the price. End-game is easily reached and 
immediately loses replayability. Needs more content and/or lowered cost.

Game is great! Super fun and I'm addicted. Only problem is the bugs, had to 
reinstall once, probably have to reinstall again. Other than that the game 
is fun as hell!

It's okay. It's not as great at people are saying. Quite repetitive, and 
once you've done the few levels, there's nothing to keep you playing. 
Annoyingly the sound effects can't be turned off so forget playing your 
Spotify in the background. Okay, but over-priced.
replyContent: I added an option to mute the sound effects in the last update. Sorry it took so long!

content: Easy concept, fantastic design, simple, yet addictive. Love it!

Yep, I got the stuck glitch as well sadly. But I'm enjoying the heck out of 
it regardless - please fix the glitch!
replyContent: I'm sorry about that. The most recent version should fix this issue. If you're still stuck you can escape a round by holding the screen with 4 fingers for 4 seconds.

content: Great fun, good time killer. Wish it had more levels and more upgrades.

Mechanics and progression are this game's strong points. I was tired of the 
mindless level based brick-and-ball games. Loved it for two days, and now 
sad that the last level is back to pointless brick-smashing with no goal. 
More progression and leveling up would elevate this to a 5-star.

The game is amazing! Love getting the right angles, so satisfying. My only 
problem lately is a bug that happens when I shoot for my first time, the 
balls glitch into one spot and I can't play anymore. If you could fix that 
would be amazing!
replyContent: I'm sorry about that. The most recent version should fix this issue. If you're still stuck you can escape a round by holding the screen with 4 fingers for 4 seconds.

content:
You know that feeling you get when you play Breakout and you get the ball 
stuck behind all of the bricks? This game is just that feeling over and 
over again.
Hypnotic mix of arkanoid and Peggle. Very good fun.

I finished the game in under a day. It's so addictive that I just see balls 
bounce in angles everywhere I look. This isn't a brain dead game and I 
really enjoy mechanics and thought process of ricocheting to reach the 
goal. Minor bugs such as floating (unfixed) shapes and etc. doesnt really 
bother but it can cause the game. I would recommend this game to kill time 
offline.

Great game but ultimately a short experience for the money. Hopefully more 
content, be it power ups or levels will be added in time to add to the 
longevity.
Great game. Wish it had a option to turn off all sounds.

Liked the game a lot but, is there a way to pause the sound all together? 
Kinda had the same problem with rimdkapzel
replyContent: I added an option to mute the sound effects in the last update. Sorry it took so long!

content: Addictive, polished.

Played non-stop for an hour after installing. This game is ridiculously 
addictive and satisfying. The sounds and visuals ooze quality.
Best in class. That little dewd in the corner is my best friend.

This is a beautifully crafted game, with its own take on the "bouncing 
brick break" genre. My only major complaint is that you can't turn off SFX 
off in-app. You can only turn off the music. There should really be an 
option to turn SFX off so that I don't have to mute my phone to play 
silently. Otherwise a great game!
All great, perfect game to spend free time!
Too good.

The game is really cool ... at first, but there's only 5 or so levels, so 
game play becomes a bit predictable after a while. (I've only had it a day) 
I'd there were more boards/challenges i would give it 5 stars, but there 
isn't, so ....

Holedown is perfect. The gameplay, sound, and visual design blend together 
to create a mobile game that's fun to play both in small chunks and for 
hours on end. If you're apprehensive about paying for mobile games, don't 
worry, this one is worth it and then some.
Incredibly satisfying.
Simple. Elegant. Addictive.

Buy this game right now! It's amazing and clever and so satisfying. If it 
was free and had in-app purchases, you'd end up getting hooked and spend 
much more than the upfront price anyways!
A ton of fun, I just hope they add more levels as more people play

Too short is my only problem! I loved it but more upgrades, a longer 
"story" etc would be great!
Very satisfying game, great for playing on the bus.

Hypnotic strategy game. Placing those balls that bounce forever is extremely satisfying and "just one more try" has never been more true than here. The minimalist sound, animations and music are there just like in the previous titles (which incidentally are all 5* material).
I lost an entire weekend to this game, it's very good, it's 100% worth the money.

Fantastic phone game! Simple, fun and can be played in short bursts. Highly 
recommended!

I picked it up instantly when I saw Terry Cavanagh recommend it on Twitter 
-- it's a delightful mix of casual and deep with great art and sound. Rogue 
Leagcy meets Breakout. Awesome!
Wonderful presentation. Audio amazing. More games like this please.
Is good. Satisfying.

Great fun, great mechanics, awesome, simple visuals. No micro-transactions 
or lootboxes, just grinding through planets and trying to nail the perfect 
angles.

Ridiculously entertaining, easy to just jump in and play. I spent about an 
hour playing without realizing it on two occasions today. Getting an angle 
just right and watching everything go wild is extremely satisfying.
Brilliant arcade game with fun progression system. Good for travelling.

Brilliant game. Easily the best of this genre. Well worth the upfront 
payment to not have to deal with micro-transactions and adverts.
Very cathartic to play!
Loving it. Can't stop hours later!
He's done it again. Absolutely perfect.

The perfect version of the 'bounce balls off things' genre. No timers or 
limits, no IAP, no DLC, no prompts to share or review, no waiting for 
energy to refill. If you want to play it for 8 hours straight, this game 
will not stop you. You will have to replay levels to earn upgrade points, 
but it never, for even a second, feels like a grind. Every run is just pure 
fun.

Easy to jump in and out of, fun and satisfying gameplay and the fantastic 
plinky plonky graphics and sound design are on par with past grapefrukt 
games.

Pros: absolutely addicting gameplay, great progression, well paced, amazing 
color and sound design Cons: few worlds, though an endless mode is available

Bought because I saw someone post a screenshot on Twitter. Very fun game, 
an interesting twist on an old mechanic, really cute visuals and worth the 
money!
The amount of juice and personality in this game is absolutely charming. The progression through upgrades while your skill itself gets better feels very well tuned.
This game is great! It's very addicting and has a lot of depth!

A perfect version of games in this genre. You get to make actual 
progression, the controls are tight, and there's an incredible amount of 
personality built in. Well worth the cost!
